This customer is 27 years old and mother to three children who all go to school. She launched herself into the patisserie business in order to provide for her family's needs and to help her husband to manage their income.Thanks to her different loans she has already bought baking tins, a traditional oven, flour and various condiments for making brioche and milk rolls. She has a turnover of between 50,000 and 120,000 francs every two days and her loans have contributed significantly to changing her family's living conditions. She has even bought a new 400 liter freezer with her profits.

With the granting of her new loan she is going to expand her business beyond patisserie to include making yoghurt and groundnut paste which she puts in pots to sell to households; to make the yoghurt she is renting a spot in a school and uses the services of a child who sells brioches and yoghurt from an ice-box.

She is very enthusiastic and aims to go far and achieve her objectives by saving a lot, so that in the long term she can create a family business;
